story.title: Fatal Consequences - Episode 4
story.storyDescription: Jo-Jo awakens, trapped in the wreckage of her car, covered in blood. The last 48 hours of her life are a blank, and the dead man beside her . . . is a total stranger.

messages.text: Who is this? How did you get this number?
The phone goes dead. Quinn hits redial.

Guilty. After I got a chance to catch my breath, I started thinking.
It only made sense you‚Äôd have a backup. The first one was clever, but the other one wasn‚Äôt hard to find.
I had to try. Better your shoe than your other shoulder.
True. Injectables are a bitch unless your subject is sedated.
Look, Jo-Jo, you‚Äôve got to let me help you. I know you don‚Äôt trust me.
Funny thing is, I do.
Why the change of heart?
Maybe I thought I‚Äôd look better in a white hat after all.
Not buying it.
I think you know why.
Because I have feelings for you.
No, because I have feelings for you.
You‚Äôre only saying that because you know I want to hear it.
Look, I‚Äôm as surprised as anyone else, but it‚Äôs true.

You know we‚Äôre never going to have a white-picket love story. That‚Äôs not who we are.

To hear your voice one more time.
Jo-Jo, please, just listen to me.
I‚Äôm tired of feeling dirty. I just want out.
I need to end this thing, and I need to be strong enough to do it on my own.

Give the senator the recording.
He needs know that his enemies are closer than he thinks‚Äî

Jo-Jo? Jo-Jo?

Subject Avery in transit to contact Leighton. She is NOT a threat.
Will intercept and detain. Advise Dante.
